Section 16: Removing Spring Boot
    Lecture 81: Remove H2 DB spring auto configuration and the create new JDBC Data source

1. Open src/main/resources/application.properties file
 1.1 add "spring.autoconfigure.exclude[1]=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.thymeleaf.DataSourceAutoConfiguration"
     property in the application.properties file

2. Setup the H2 DataSource using JDBC
 2.1 Create new H2DataSourceConfig.java
    - ej.springframework.config.H2DataSourceConfig.java
 2.2 Add spring context @Configuration annotation above the H2DataSourceConfig class
 2.3 Implements H2DataSourceConfig class

3. Test
  3.1 Start Server
  3.2 Open H2-console browser
  3.3 login and check the testdb data sources (i.e, PRODUCT Table)